question: Those in HS/College, was it/is it required to do community service?
comment:
It wasn't required for the general school population for me. In high school I had to do 60 hours as part of National Honor Society, but had I not joined then I wouldn't of had to do it.

I think it was inconvenient but in the end it was kind of fun because you can choose the community service you do. I did some helping the homeless but most of my time was at the animal shelter, playing with dogs and cats all day lol.

I don't think it should be required for the whole school, but I don't see an issue for NHS or organizations like that to require it. And I do think teachers should be allowed to offer some extra credit to kids who volunteer. Community service is a great way to see part of the world and your community that needs help and is in poor condition, but in a safe and controlled manner. It won't do this for all kids but some kids may even be shocked by what they see and want to do more, to help, or develop future plans to better the community. There is little downside to it because they have the option of not doing it, but there is an incentive to complete it with extra credit, so there might be some who take the opportunity to do so.
